U
U^*AU = \Lambda
\Lambda = \operatorname{diag}(\lambda_1,...,\lambda_n)
\lambda_k \ge 0
\Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}} = \operatorname{diag}(\sqrt{\lambda_1},...,\sqrt{\lambda_n})
(\Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}})^* = \Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}}
A = U \Lambda U^* = U \Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}} \Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}} U^*= U \Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}} (\Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}})^* U^* = U \Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}} ( U \Lambda^{\frac{1}{2}})^*
